Why self-immolation?
- Initial observations considered it due to depression and despair.
    - not actually true
- Alternative view -- trying to awaken consciousness of those in authority
    - did not fit the ideology of Tibetans
- Dalai Lama did not show support or influence towards the movement

Dalai Lama - meaningful autonomy in Tibet
Many Tibetans undergo great pains to show their emotions or feelings. There may not
be any emotions or rationale behind these, but they may be comparable to a scream.


